  "text": "Discussion. The effect of OSL on information search in the curiosity condition was in the expected direction, but it was not very strong. One reason for this may be that the experiment was too abstract and/ or that the task-set manipulation (choice vs. curiosity) was not strong enough. It is interesting that Raju (1980) also found that OSL was only weakly related to information seeking. Another reason might therefore be that it is very difficult to separate true exploratory information seeking from goal-directed information seeking. [CITATION_1] has suggested that exploratory information seeking might serve two purposes, stimulation and use in future decision making, and this may also account for the weak effects found in the present study.",
